Really cute "Ch-Irish" bar across from Second City in Old Town. They have 3 different spaces. 1: The bar you walk into, which is a pretty typical Irish bar with booth seating. 2: Then walk towards the door in the back for outdoor seating. Very cute patio with heaters when it's chilly. 3: then walk thru the patio to another little bar with high top seating. Food was great, we got the Parmesan truffle fries, the fish and chips (opted for the homemade kettle chips instead of fries), the southwest salad and the quesedillas and they were all good! Highly recommend if you are in the area and need a quick (but sit-down) bite to eat.
